 1> DNS (Domain Name System) = DNS covert domain name into an IP address.
 
 ~ Humans remebers domain names easily.
 ~ Computers communicate using IP addresses.

 Example = google.com = 142.301.110


 2> Domain Name 

 = A domain name is the human readable name of website.

 ~ it helps users access websites without remembering
    IP addresses.

 ~ Eveey domain points to an IP address through DNS.

 Example = google.com


 3> HTTP vs HTTPS

 # HTTP ( Hypertext Transfer protocol)

 ~ Used for communication between browser and server.

 ~ Data is not encrypted.

 ~ Not secure.

 # HTTPS (HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure)

 ~ Secure version of HTTP.
 ~ Data is encrypted
 ~ Protects sensitive information during communication.

  # Default Ports
  
   HTTP = Port 80
   HTTPS = Port 443


 4> Ports

 = A port is logical communication endpoint.

 ~ it tells the operating system which service
   or application should receive the network request.

 ~ One IP address can have multiple services running on different ports.


 5> SSH (Secure Shell)

  = SSH is a secure protocol used to remotely access and
    manage Linux servers.

  ~ Communication is encrypted.
  
  ~ Commonly used to connect to AWS EC2 instances.


 6> Commands
 
 # curl -I https://google.com 

 = For check website status or server information.

 # ssh -V
  
 = For checking SSH version or SSH is installed in system or not
